Project Context: Trainee Management System

1. Project Vision
The Trainee Management System is designed to provide transparency and structure to the internship/training process. It facilitates interaction between Mentors and Trainees through automated task assignments, structured daily progress reporting, and performance tracking. Formal numeric grading and primary written feedback are tied to a weekly cycle and a weekly performance summary—not to approving or scoring each individual daily report.

2. User Roles & Responsibilities

Role A: Trainee (The Learner)
Task Management: View assigned tasks derived from a specific training curriculum.

Daily Reporting:
- Submit a Daily Report following the canonical template below (plain text / markdown-friendly; may be produced by a form that renders the same layout).
- After submit, the Trainee may continue to edit the report until the system’s weekly aggregation job locks that reporting window for the week (see Workflow).
- Optionally log man-hours spent on specific tasks when the product persists per-task hours (e.g. daily_report_task_hours); this is supplementary to the narrative template.

Canonical Daily Report template (order and section titles):
1) Title line: Daily Report < DD/MM/YYYY > (report date).
2) Fresher line: Fresher: <Full name> Day <N> (N = training day index per company convention).
3) Separator (e.g. a line of dashes).
4) Nội dung công việc hôm nay: bullet list (-), one item per work item completed today.
5) Separator.
6) Nội dung công việc ngày mai: bullet list (-), planned work for the next day.
7) Separator.
8) Khó khăn: short text (e.g. N/A or a brief description).
9) Separator.
10) Reference links block (e.g. markdown-style lines with > prefix): Trello, Github, Drive — one URL each where applicable, or an explicit “none” if allowed by policy.

Progress Tracking: Monitor personal completion rates; formal mentor scores and weekly comments appear after each week’s summary is available.

Q&A: Send direct inquiries to Mentors regarding specific tasks or blockers.

Role B: Mentor (The Supervisor)
Curriculum Management: Create training roadmaps (Curricula) by uploading learning materials (PDFs) and defining task templates.

Review & Governance:
- Daily reports: Mentors may read daily submissions for awareness or informal guidance; there is no requirement to approve, reject, or grade each daily report. Optional qualitative follow-up (outside the weekly grade) is allowed if the product supports it.
- Weekly grading: After the system runs the scheduled weekly aggregation and produces or updates the Weekly Performance Summary for an assignment/week, the Mentor provides the official weekly score and feedback for that week (not per-day numeric grades tied to closing each daily).

Monitoring (Dashboard): Track the real-time status of all assigned Trainees to identify those who are falling behind or facing critical issues.

Account Management: Manage Trainee profiles and system access.

3. Core Business Workflow
Onboarding: A Mentor creates a Trainee account and assigns a specific Curriculum. The system automatically generates a list of Tasks for that Trainee based on the curriculum templates.

Daily execution: The Trainee works on tasks and maintains Daily Reports using the canonical template. Reports move through draft/submit as implemented; submitted content remains editable by the Trainee until the weekly cutoff enforced by the system’s weekly aggregation job.

Notifications: When a Trainee submits (or re-submits) a Daily Report, an automated notification may be sent to the Mentor via external Chatops (e.g., Slack/Discord) as a reminder—without implying that each submission must be graded or approved the same day.

Weekly aggregation (system): On a schedule (implementation milestone: scheduled job), the system aggregates the week’s daily data into a Weekly Performance Summary for mentor review. This job also defines when daily content for that week becomes immutable (“weekly lock”).

Weekly mentor review: Only after the weekly summary exists for that week, the Mentor records official weekly grading and feedback on that summary—not as a mandatory step after every daily submit.

4. Key Logic Constraints
Daily reports: While the reporting window for the week is open, Trainees may edit submitted daily content (including after “submit”) until the weekly aggregation job locks that week; after the lock, daily rows for that week are immutable.

Grading: Official scores and primary mentor feedback attach to the weekly performance summary (or equivalent entity), not to closing each daily report with a grade.

Consistency: When man-hours per task are used, they must remain linked to tasks under the active assignment/curriculum so effort rolls up correctly into weekly summaries.

Automation: Task generation must be handled by the system immediately upon curriculum assignment to prevent manual entry errors.

Implementation note (database): The persistence layer may still use enums or columns (e.g. on daily_reports) that differ from the UX above until migrated; product behavior in this document takes precedence, and engineering should align schema and status transitions in a later change set.
